propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propComponent:
The component used for the root node.
Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.
propDense:
If `true`, compact vertical padding designed for keyboard and mouse input is used for
the list and list items.
The prop is available to descendant components as the `dense` context.
propDisablePadding: If `true`, vertical padding is removed from the list.
propSubheader: The content of the subheader, normally `ListSubheader`.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesPadding: Styles applied to the root element unless `disablePadding={true}`.
stylesDense: Styles applied to the root element if dense.
stylesSubheader: Styles applied to the root element if a `subheader` is provided.
